{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "05", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "08", "M": "37", "S": "53"}}, "news": [{"title": "Ludhiana: LIT slashes reserve price to \u20b9182 crore in fresh bid to auction its commercial building", "para": "Ludhiana Improvement Trust has slashed the reserve price of a prime commercial building by \u20b915 crore to \u20b9182 crore in a fresh e-auction, hoping to attract buyers after previous attempts failed. The 18-year-old, abandoned property, featuring extensive commercial space and parking, has suffered from neglect. LIT is also considering price cuts for other properties due to poor market response.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/ludhiana-improvement-trust-reduces-auction-price-of-prime-commercial-building-to-182-crore/132191743?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-192338/132191743.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "NCLT directs Entertainment City to register minority stake in favour of Parmesh Construction", "para": "Insolvency tribunal NCLT has greenlit Parmesh Construction Company's acquisition of a 4.26% stake in Entertainment City, dismissing Unitech Holding's objections. The tribunal ruled that the share transfer by minority investors was valid, despite Unitech's claims of violated shareholder agreements. This decision stems from a broader 100% disinvestment process for Entertainment City, where Parmesh Construction emerged as the successful bidder.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/nclt-rules-in-favor-of-parmesh-construction-against-unitech-in-entertainment-city-stake-dispute/132191679?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-448636/132191679.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Manesar civic body razes six concrete plants, 30 more under scanner", "para": "Authorities in Gurugram have intensified their crackdown on illegal operations, demolishing six ready-mix concrete plants on Garhi-Basai Road for lacking mandatory permissions. This action follows a similar demolition last week. Despite these efforts, over 30 unauthorized plants remain operational, raising concerns about regulatory oversight. Officials vow to take action against all remaining illegal establishments, urging businesses to secure necessary approvals before commencing operations.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/cement/manesar-civic-body-razes-six-concrete-plants-30-more-under-scanner/132191388?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1739049/132191388.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "cement"}]}